title: Week 6: Operation Sports Fantasy Football Championship on FanDuel
text: Week 6: Operation Sports Fantasy Football Championship on FanDuel 03:38 PM - October 15, 2015 by Steve_OS With five weeks of the NFL season in the books, its about time we figure out which teams truly are good and which teams are truly bad. Thats what happened in Week 5. The Atlanta Falcons, truly good. The Detroit Lions, truly bad. The Cincinnati Bengals, truly good. The Jacksonville Jaguars, truly bad (OK, maybe we already knew that). Before we recap the winning lineup from Week 5 of The Operation Sports FanDuel Championship , heres what you need to know about Week 6: The contest costs $5 to play and pays $100 to first place. Click here to enter! We'll see you there! The winning lineup from Week 5, submitted by bmore_irish, received a huge boost from big performances by Devonta Freeman, Justin Forsett and old man Gates, Antonio Gates! bmore_irish finished with 176.20 points, handily defeating the rest of the field by nearly 20 points. Finishing second in Week 5 is luth58, who just so happened to win the Week 4 contest. Way to be, luth58!
